{"word":"ὅσπερ","slug":"ὅσπερ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὅσπερ</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the very man who, the very thing which</i>, but often simply for <el>ὅς</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <el>ἅπερ</el>, <i>as</i>, like <el>καθάπερ</el> (<a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:καθά'><el>καθά</el></a>), <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ᾗπερ</el>, <i>which way, where, whither</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; ionic <el>τῇπερ· </el> — also <i>as</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}